# InterviewGuru splits environment by layer:
#
#   backend/.env   → GROQ_API_KEY, CLERK_SECRET_KEY, DATABASE_URL (single Postgres), PORT, …
#   frontend/.env  → VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY, GEMINI_API_KEY, VITE_API_URL
#
# Quick start:
#   cp backend/.env.example backend/.env
#   cp frontend/.env.example frontend/.env
#
# Production: set Clerk + Postgres on the server, and Clerk publishable key at Vite build time.
# Optional: ABUSE_MAX_SIGNUPS_PER_IP_PER_DAY on the server to limit throwaway accounts.
#
# Legacy: a root `.env` still loads first; `backend/.env` overrides duplicate keys.
